(a) Align the No. 2 roof headlining pad with the markings on the roof headlining assembly and install it using hot-melt glue as shown in the illustration.

(c) Engage each clamp.

(d) Align the marking tape (A) on the No. 1 roof wire with the tab on the front side of the roof headlining assembly.

(e) Align the edge of each marking tape (B) on the No. 1 roof wire with each notch on the roof headlining assembly.

(f) w/ Sliding Roof:

(1) Align the edge of the marking tape (C) on the No. 1 roof wire with the marking on the roof headlining assembly.

(g) Attach the No. 1 roof wire with the butyl tape.

NOTICE:

  • Securely attach the No. 1 roof wire.
  • If any of the No. 1 roof wire is left loose, it will cause an abnormal noise.
  • Make sure to attach the No. 1 roof wire without leaving any of it loose.

HINT:

Secure the extra length of the No. 1 roof wire in the adjustment area.

(h) Install the No. 1 roof wire to the roof headlining assembly with adhesive tape.

w/o Sliding Roof

NOTICE:

  • Apply the tape securely in place.
  • Do not touch the adhesive surface when applying the tape to prevent adhesion failure.

8. INSTALL VANITY LIGHT ASSEMBLY

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

(a) Engage the claw (B) to install the vanity light assembly.

*a

*b

(b) Engage the 2 claws (A) to install the bulb holder to the vanity light assembly.
